1. In a bowl, reserve 2 tablespoons each of the tomato, cucumber, pepper, and onion to garnish. 2. In the food processor or blender, pur√©e the remaining ingredients (except the croutons) until smooth, adjusting the seasoning to taste with lemon juice, salt, and cayenne pepper. 3. Cover and chill thoroughly, at least 3 hours but preferably overnight. Adjust the consistency as desired with water. Serve in chilled bowls garnished with the reserved vegetables and croutons.